absolutus est.’ ‘ Cum Capitolio praeesset coronam rapuit. Ex crimine Capito- linus Petillius vocabatur.' The account is discredited by two facts, (1) Capito- linus is known to have been a proper ‘cognomen’ in the gens Petillia. (2) The crime of robbing Capitoline Jove of his crown is proverbial as early as Plautus, Trin. 1. 2. 46, Menaechm. 5. 5. 38. See Introd. to Satires, p. 9.
